<h1 style="text-align:center;">microscope.js : nodejs framework for ASP MVC developper</h1>

<p>Modify this template to jump-start your Node.JS microscope application</p>
<h3>We suggest the following:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>
    <h5>Scaffolding engine</h5>
    <p>Open your shell in the root of your microscope project and type the following command : 
      </br><pre>node microscope.js generate_crud article title:string content:text </pre>
    </p>
    <p>microscope scaffolding engine allow you to create controller, api, services, model and views quickly for rapid development.</p>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h5>Try this out on a mobile device</h5>
    <p>microscope framework supports various template options for viewing on mobile devices as recommend in Node.js Webmatrix samples.</p>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h5>The power of JavaScript</h5>
    <p>microscope framework come with a large choice of JavaScript librairies. <a href="http://jquerymobile.com/">jQuery Mobile</a> (Touch-Optimized Web Framework for Smartphones & Tablets), 
      <a href="http://jquery.com/">jQuery</a> (DOM/Ajax manipulation), <a href="http://knockoutjs.com/">knockout</a> (client-side MVVM pattern), <a href="https://github.com/CodeSeven/toastr">toastr</a> (notifications).</p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <h5>Authentication</h5>
    <p>microscope framework use <b>passport.js</b> to perform user authentication with locals or with oAuth data.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

